How to Update Video Card Drivers on     Windows 7

00:00:10.400 --> 00:00:16.300
Click on the start Menu and go to Control Panel.

00:00:16.300 --> 00:00:31.400
Click on "Device manager".

00:00:31.400 --> 00:00:46.900
In this menu you should see a section called "Display adapters" click on it.

00:00:46.900 --> 00:00:52.566
Now right click on the video card shown and select "Update Driver Software".

00:00:52.566 --> 00:00:55.666
Then select Search automatically.

00:00:55.666 --> 00:01:00.832
If Windows 7 found a driver, Click Install and then restart your computer.

00:01:00.833 --> 00:01:06.266
As all the necessary drivers has been installed on my pc, i am getting this message. 

00:01:06.266 --> 00:01:07.666
 

00:01:07.666 --> 00:01:10.932
Updating Driver Manually.

00:01:10.933 --> 00:01:20.599
To update the drivers manually, write down the name of the video card from the "Device manager" menu under "Display adapters".

00:01:20.600 --> 00:01:21.833
 

00:01:21.833 --> 00:01:36.133
Now, Open your Favorite browser and Search for the driver in Google.

00:01:36.133 --> 00:01:40.366
 

00:01:40.366 --> 00:01:46.699
You will be redirected to the manufacturer's website.

00:01:46.700 --> 00:01:52.700
Here Select your operating system.

00:01:52.700 --> 00:02:01.300
Now click on the downloads links to download the latest version of the driver to your computer.

00:02:01.300 --> 00:02:06.800
Click on the download now button.

00:02:06.800 --> 00:02:12.000
Accept the terms and condition to continue with download process.

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:20.266
Wait until the file is downloaded to your computer.

00:02:20.266 --> 00:02:27.999
Once the download completes, double click on the file to start the installation process. 

00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:33.433
Follow the on screen instructions.

00:02:33.433 --> 00:02:38.499
 

00:02:38.500 --> 00:02:43.233
Restart Your computer to apply the changes.

00:02:43.233 --> 00:02:47.166
This is How You can Update Video Card Drivers on Windows 7

